cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper focuses on predicting the memorability of visual content, which is a core problem in computer vision. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The dataset used in the paper is composed of videos, which falls under the domain of multimedia. 
3. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with the retrieval of information from visual content, specifically predicting the memorability of videos. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes several deep neural network-based models for predicting video memorability, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper also discusses the human tendency to memorize/forget visual information, which is a core problem in human-computer interaction.
